    "body": "I see your point. I think we can achieve by a customizable Cap Strategy. Currently, we have a single Cap but it may be defined per block or time period. What's your view on that?\r\n\r\nBTW, I've just looked at the CappedCrowdsale and realised that we require the last transaction to precisely hit the capped target. It can bring a lot of frustration to users burning gas by trying to put the final transaction. The common behaviour is to return part of the donation that is above the cap as soon as it's exceeded. Should we create an issue and fix this? ",
