    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@jakub-wojciechowski Let's stay on-topic and discuss only continuous crowdsales here. 🙂 We can talk about the \"precise cap\" problem in a different issue. (I'm not sure we want to implement the partial refund.)\r\n\r\nWe should be careful not to conflate the different kinds of limits a crowdsale can have. \"Continuous\" refers to the lack of a limit in the crowdsale's _running time_. \"Capped\", OTOH, refers to the limit in the amount of _money_ that can be raised.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure I understand how the issuance model should be part of the logic of a ContinuousCrowdsale contract. Would it make sense to not restrict issuance in any way, and let that happen elsewhere?",
