    "body": "Yes, you are right lets move \"precise cap\" to a different issue. \r\n\r\nI agree, let's separate time boundaries and issuance model and decide what to do with the first problem.\r\n\r\nIf we stick to the inheritance model, continuous crowdsale seems to be a parent to a current `Crowdsale` as it is more generic by not imposing any limitation for `startBlock` and `endBlock`. I see the refactor as extracing all logic that handles time boundaries to a sublass 'FixedCrowdsale' and our base `Crowdsale` will automatically become a continuous one. ",
